## 2. Search Intent & Target Audience

The searcher is a first-time renter or someone returning to the rental market after several years who needs a comprehensive, procedural roadmap — not a single-step answer. They are in the **early-to-mid consideration stage**, have identified renting as their housing path, and are now trying to understand the full process before committing money or time. They are specifically trying to solve the problem of not knowing what steps to take, what documents to gather, how much money to have ready, and what to watch out for legally and financially. They expect a **sequential how-to guide** with clear numbered steps, checklists, and direct answers to cost and eligibility questions.

